@kxll-yi6nq Market share is the total sales or units sold compared to the total industry over a given period of time. For the month of March to date, AMD has a market share of 45%. I don't doubt their market share will shrink to 80% if you go back further, though.

Total percentage of quantity of each product in use is probably ownership rate or usage share. But market rate generally refers to the market--where products are currently being sold, not what's currently in people's computer.

IE, it doesn't matter if Nvidia 1060 6gb is still in 6% of people's computers, it has a 0% market share in the past 7 or so years for Nvidia as they probably aren't selling them.

